---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Developers">
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <h1 class="hero__text heading--1">Interledger Developers Portal</h1>
        <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img src="/developers/img/devs.svg" alt="Illustration of developers working at a table" class="hero__img" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <p class="heading--4">Learn more about the various open-source projects that Interledger is working on.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="content-wrapper cards">
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="heading--5">Open Payments</h2>
          <p>Open Payments is an open API standard that can be implemented by account servicing entities to facilitate interoperability in the setup and completion of payments for different use cases.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/interledger/open-payments">Learn more on Github</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="heading--5">Rafiki</h2>
          <p>Rafiki is open source software that provides a more efficient method for an account servicing entity to enable Interledger functionality on its users' accounts.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/interledger/rafiki">Learn more on Github</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="heading--5">Specifications</h2>
          <p>The Interledger Protocol (ILP) is an open, neutral protocol for transferring money based on TCP/IP, designed for sending packets of money across different accounting ledgers. <a href="/developers/rfcs/interledger-protocol/">Read</a> the Interledger specifications or <a href="https://github.com/interledger/rfcs">contribute</a> to them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="heading--5">Test Network</h2>
          <p>The Test Network (Testnet) is an open Interledger network working with test money designed for account servicing entities to test their Interledger integration.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/interledger/testnet">Learn more on Github</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 class="heading--5">Engineering Blog</h2>
          <p>Our team shares theirs thoughts and experiences on Interledger and the work that we are doing.</p>
          <a href="/developers/blog">Read our blog</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main {
    padding-block-end: var(--space-l);
  }

  section {
    padding-block-start: var(--space-l);
  }

  section:last-child {
    padding-block-end: var(--space-l);
  }
  .hero {
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: bottom right;
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, #007777, #69BCC3);
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, oklch(51.54% 0.088 194.77), oklch(74.53% 0.082 202.65));
    min-height: 60vh;
    padding-block: var(--space-m);
    color: var(--color-white);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-m);
  }

  .hero__text {
    flex: 3;
    color: var(--color-white);
    font-weight: 600;
    max-width: 10em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-block-end: var(--space-2xs);
  }

  .image-wrapper {
    flex: 0 1 auto;
    max-width: 30rem;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 799px) {
    .hero {
      padding-block: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .hero .content-wrapper {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
  
  .cards {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .card {
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    margin-inline: auto;
    box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
    padding: var(--space-xs) var(--space-s);
    background-color: var(--color-white);
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 800px) {
    .card {
      flex: 1 1 calc(50% - var(--space-m));
    }
  }

  .card h2 {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .card h2,
  .card p {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-3xs);
  }

  .card a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .card a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
